	 <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
		<head>Historical Statement</head>
	<p>The Metropolitan Medical Society was founded in 1861 with the goal of advancing medical science and facilitating social relationships among members through presentations, discussions, and an exchange of ideas. Meetings were hosted 9 months out of the year at the residences of members.</p>
	 </bioghist> 
	 <scopecontent encodinganalog="520"> 
		<head>Scope and Content</head> 
		<p>The majority of the collection is comprised of minutes from the monthly meetings (1892-1963), and also includes several programs, letters, treasurer's reports, and other assorted documents.</p> 
	 </scopecontent> 	  
	 <arrangement>
		<head>Arrangement of Collection</head>
		<p>The meeting minutes are in chronological order within several folders and notebooks. Loose documents have been divided by document type with the original chronological order preserved.</p>
	 </arrangement>
